'''David Crane''' read history and English at [[Oxford University]] before becoming a lecturer at universities in the [[Netherlands]],
[[Japan]], and [[Africa]]. He lives in northwest [[Scotland]].

He has written two books about [[Lord Byron]] and his family; a biography of explorer [[Robert Falcon Scott]]; and a book about World War I grave monuments.

