|[[File:St Mary's church, Sandwich - geograph.org.uk - 1235728.jpg|100px|alt=A flint and stone church with a tiled roof]]
| style="text-align:center;"|{{sort|1050|11th&nbsp;century}}
|St Mary's has suffered from repeated damage: by the French in 1217 and again in 1457, and from an earthquake in 1578.  In 1667 the central tower collapsed, and was rebuilt.  In the 19th&nbsp;century the church was [[Victorian restoration|restored]] by [[Joseph Clarke (architect)|Joseph Clarke]].  Since being made redundant it has been used as an arts centre.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/visit/church-listing/st-mary-sandwich.html | title = St Mary's Church, Sandwich, Kent | accessdate = 15 October 2016 | publisher = [[Churches Conservation Trust]]}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1069541|desc= St Mary's Church, Sandwich|accessdate= 28 March 2015|mode=cs2|ps=none|fewer-links=x}}</ref><ref name=hist>{{Citation | url = http://www.open-sandwich.co.uk/places_to_visit/churches/stmarys.htm| title = St. Mary's Church| accessdate = 14 May 2011| publisher = Sandwich History Society}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | url = http://www.stmarysartscentre.org.uk/venue.htm| title = St. Mary's Venue| accessdate = 14 May 2011| publisher = Sandwich St. Mary's Community Trust}}</ref>
