|The [[chancel]] was added later in the 12th&nbsp;century, and the windows date from the 15th and 16th&nbsp;centuries.  The church was [[Victorian restoration|restored]] twice in the 19th&nbsp;century.  Inside the church is a [[Norman architecture|Norman]] [[baptismal font|font]].  There is a painting of a saint in the splay of one of the windows.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/visit/church-listing/st-mary-ashley.html | title = St Mary's Church, Ashley, Hampshire| accessdate = 15 October 2016 | publisher = [[Churches Conservation Trust]]}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1339063|desc= Church of St Mary, Ashley|accessdate= 28 March 2015|mode=cs2|ps=none|fewer-links=x}}</ref>
