|[[Kent]]<br/><small>{{Coord|51.3332|0.4170|name=St Benedict, Paddlesworth}}</small>
|[[File:St Benedict's Church - geograph.org.uk - 19933.jpg|100px|alt=A very simple barn-like stone church with a tiled roof]]
| style="text-align:center;"|{{sort|1125|Early 12th&nbsp;century}}
|This simple church stands on the [[Pilgrims' Way]].  It closed as a church in 1678 and was then used for some 250&nbsp;years for non-religious purposes, including use as a farm building.  A gallery was added in the 19th&nbsp;century, and the church was restored twice during the 20th&nbsp;century.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/visit/church-listing/st-benedict-paddlesworth.html | title = St Benedict's Church, Paddlesworth, Kent | accessdate = 15 October 2016 | publisher = [[Churches Conservation Trust]]}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1363120|desc= Church of St Benedict, Snodland|accessdate= 28 March 2015|mode=cs2|ps=none|fewer-links=x}}</ref>
