|St Mary's stands in an isolated position.  A stone [[chancel]] arch was added in the 14th&nbsp;century containing a three-[[bay (architecture)|bay]] [[arcade (architecture)|arcade]]. Above the arcade is a large round-headed opening that silhouetted the [[rood]] cross, a feature unique in England.  The church also contains a memorial to General Sir&nbsp;[[Charles William Dunbar Staveley]], who died in 1896.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/visit/church-listing/st-mary-capel-le-ferne.html | title = St Mary's Church, Capel-le-Ferne, Kent| accessdate = 15 October 2016 | publisher = [[Churches Conservation Trust]]}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1070047|desc= Church of St Mary, Capel le Ferne|accessdate= 28 March 2015|mode=cs2|ps=none|fewer-links=x}}</ref>
