|The [[mausoleum]] was added to the north side of the church of [[St. Lawrence, Little Stanmore|St Lawrence Whitchurch]] for the [[James Brydges, 1st Duke of Chandos|1st Duke of Chandos]] in 1735.  It was designed by [[James Gibbs]], and contains memorials to members of the Chandos family.  The church itself continues to be in active use, and the mausoleum is vested in the Trust.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.visitchurches.org.uk/visit/church-listing/chandos-mausoleum-little-stanmore.html | title = Chandos Mausoleum (St Lawrence's Church), Little Stanmore, London | accessdate = 15 October 2016 | publisher = [[Churches Conservation Trust]]}}</ref><ref>{{NHLE |num= 1194471|desc= Church of St Lawrence, Harrow|accessdate= 28 March 2015|mode=cs2|ps=none|fewer-links=x}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url= http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=26924|title= Little Stanmore: Church|accessdate= 18 May 2011|editor1-last= Baker|editor1-first= T. F. T.|editor2-last= Pugh|editor2-first= R. B.  |work= A History of the County of Middlesex|volume = 5 |year=1976 |series = [[Victoria County History]] |publisher= University of London & History of Parliament Trust |pages= 122–124}}</ref>
