'''Randall Gregory Holcombe''' (born June 4, 1950) is an American [[economist]], and the DeVoe Moore Professor of Economics at [[Florida State University]].<ref name=fsu_0>Florida State University, [http://www.coss.fsu.edu/economics/people/faculty Economics Department faculty listing] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719203811/http://www.coss.fsu.edu/economics/people/faculty |date=2011-07-19 }}. Retrieved 2011-02-01.</ref> He is a Research Fellow at [[The Independent Institute]],<ref name=tii_0>The Independent Institute, [http://www.independent.org/aboutus/person_detail.asp?id=528 Randall G. Holcombe]. Retrieved 2012-04-18.</ref> a Senior Fellow and member of the Research Advisory Council at [[James Madison Institute|The James Madison Institute]],<ref>The James Madison Institute, [http://www.jamesmadison.org/about/research-advisory-council.html#randall_holcombe Research Advisory Council]. Retrieved 2012-04-18.</ref> and past president of the Public Choice Society.<ref name=fsu_1>Florida State University, [http://www.coss.fsu.edu/economics/people/randall-g-holcombe Randall G. Holcombe] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419004836/http://www.coss.fsu.edu/economics/people/randall-g-holcombe |date=2012-04-19 }}. Retrieved 2012-04-18.</ref> From 2000 to 2006 he served on [[List of Governors of Florida|Governor]] [[Jeb Bush|Jeb Bush's]] Council of Economic Advisors.<ref name=fsu_1 />
Holcombe is the author of several books on [[economics]] and [[Politics of the United States|American politics]].<ref name=tii_0 /> In [[Libertarianism|libertarian]] theoretical discourse, he has argued that [[private defense agency|private defense agencies]] could form cartels and oppress people, more or less as governments, with little fear of competition.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Government: Unnecessary but Inevitable|author=Holcombe, Randall G.|url=http://www.independent.org/pdf/tir/tir_08_3_1_holcombe.pdf}}</ref>
Holcombe is a musician and licensed pilot.<ref>Mises Economics Blog, [http://archive.mises.org/14612/faculty-spotlight-interview-randall-g-holcombe/]. Retrieved 2012-04-18.</ref>
